HEADWORD: gosan-chiku
<hw>gosan-chiku</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A small bamboo
of Southeastern China (<spn>Phyllostachys aurea</spn>) having slender
culms flexuous when young.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> fishpole bamboo, hotei-chiku, <spn>Phyllostachys
aurea</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
